csvOpener: Can you beat your opponent to the your place as a dojo master?
csvDescription: This game will require players to use their left and right keys to climb lines of rope to the segment that they think the dojo master wants. Be careful not to fall down as you try and figure out exactly what colour he means!
csvIntent: To make updates on some of my former university work based on new knowledge.

csvOpener: The way out of the maze is clear. That is, if you can read the room.
csvDescription: Use the arrow keys to move from the top left corner to the bottom right. You will only be allowed to move in one direction for each space you land on, so pay close attention to the colour guide on the menu. How many rooms can you clear before the time runs out?
csvIntent: To make updates on my submission for Grads In Games' "Search For A Star" competition.

csvName: Autonomous Movement from a Double Robot
csvOpener: The Double Robot is a device that allows users to control its movements while accessing a video stream from the camera of an iPad attached at the top. Myself and a group of students from the Nottingham Trent Developers Society (DevSoc) attempted to use the camera to control the robot's movement, basing its decisions on a 'target' with a set colour value.
csvDescription: The potential benefit of this would be that it could be used to follow leaders of touring groups, around the university or otherwise, and then provide the iPad as a visual aide for them to interact with.
csvIntent: To assess my progress with working in a collaboration on unfamiliar technologies during my degree course
